"title": "5145: clothing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5145",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Garments were originally provided by God for Adam and Eve. Kings and priests were given special garments. God's people should neither be unduly anxious about how they dress, nor judge others by what they wear. Inner clothing is more important than outer adornment.</p>\n<h2>The origin of clothing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:21\">GEN 3:21</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Various regulations regarding clothing</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:1-Lev15:27\">LEV 15:1–15:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:5\">DEU 22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:11-Deut22:12\">DEU 22:11–22:12</a></p>\n<h2>Special clothing for priests</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1-Exod28:5\">EXO 28:1–28:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:5-Exod29:6\">EXO 29:5–29:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:1\">EXO 39:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7-Lev8:9\">LEV 8:7–8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:17-Ezek44:19\">EZK 44:17–44:19</a></p>\n<h2>Rich clothing a sign of wealth or status</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:42\">GEN 41:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:18\">2SA 13:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:8-Esth6:9\">EST 6:8–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:15\">EST 8:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:13-Ps45:14\">PSA 45:13–45:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:19\">LUK 16:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:21\">ACT 12:21</a></p>\n<h2>The Israelites' clothing did not wear out in the desert wanderings</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:4\">DEU 8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:5\">DEU 29:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:21\">NEH 9:21</a></p>\n<h2>Clothing as a symbol of fragility and perishability</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:8\">ISA 51:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:9\">ISA 50:9</a></p>\n<h2>Symbolic actions involving clothing</h2>\n<h3>The hem or corner of a garment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:9\">RUT 3:9</a> <em>The corner of a garment spread over a person denotes protection and possession.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20\">MAT 9:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:44\">LUK 8:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:17\">JHN 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:27\">1SA 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:4-1Sam24:5\">1SA 24:4–24:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:29\">GEN 37:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:34\">GEN 37:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:13\">GEN 44:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:6\">LEV 10:6</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:31\">2SA 3:31</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Provision of rich clothing a picture of God's love</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:10-Ezek16:13\">EZK 16:10–16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:22\">LUK 15:22</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of unusual clothing</h2>\n<h3>Joseph's richly ornamented robe</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3\">GEN 37:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:23\">GEN 37:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:32\">GEN 37:32</a></p>\n<h3>The dress of Elijah and John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:8\">2KI 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:4\">MAT 3:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:6\">MRK 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Isaiah's lack of clothing a prophetic sign</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa20:2-Isa20:4\">ISA 20:2–20:4</a></p>\n<h3>The mock robing of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:28\">MAT 27:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:17\">MRK 15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:2\">JHN 19:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:11\">LUK 23:11</a></p>\n<h3>Gambling at the cross for Jesus Christ's clothing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24\">MRK 15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:23-John19:24\">JHN 19:23–19:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:18\">PSA 22:18</a></p>\n<h2>Women and clothing</h2>\n<h3>Women praised for making clothing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:21\">PRO 31:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:24\">PRO 31:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:39\">ACT 9:39</a></p>\n<h3>Women urged to dress modestly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:9\">1TI 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:3\">1PE 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>Believers not to be unduly anxious about clothing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:28-Matt6:30\">MAT 6:28–6:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:27-Luke12:28\">LUK 12:27–12:28</a></p>\n<h2>Believers not to discriminate because of clothing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:1-Jas2:4\">JAS 2:1–2:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Inner clothing more important than outer adornment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:3-1Pet3:4\">1PE 3:3–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:25\">PRO 31:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:1\">ISA 52:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:3\">ISA 61:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:9-1Tim2:10\">1TI 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>The robe of righteousness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:14\">JOB 29:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:9\">PSA 132:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:16\">PSA 132:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:3-Zech3:5\">ZEC 3:3–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:1-Matt22:14\">MAT 22:1–22:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:2-2Cor5:4\">2CO 5:2–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:17-Rev3:18\">REV 3:17–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:8\">REV 19:8</a></p>\n<h2>White clothing, the clothing of heaven</h2>\n<h3>The transfiguration of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:3\">MRK 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:29\">LUK 9:29</a></p>\n<h3>The angels at the tomb</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:3\">MAT 28:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:5\">MRK 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:4\">LUK 24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:12\">JHN 20:12</a></p>\n<h3>The vision of the redeemed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:4-Rev3:5\">REV 3:4–3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:18\">REV 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:4\">REV 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:11\">REV 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a></p>\n<h3>The vision of the exalted Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:13\">REV 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:13\">REV 19:13</a></p>",
